metadata.name: Luminous Ocean #6
metadata.description:
Luminous Ocean is a collection based on the bioluminescence phenomenon, in this case the one produced in the ocean.
I used the Flow Fields concept to create it.

There are 18 color palettes for the spheres and rings, which have 2 types of sizes, medium and small.
70% of the background is black.
20% chance that the background will change.
5% chance that the spheres and rings will be bright multicolored.
2% chance of getting a super rare ocean.

Press "S" in live mode to save image 1600x2000.

Created by Fernando. NFT License 2.0.

metadata.name: Generative Charts #02 #358
metadata.description:
Click and drag to adjust camera. Hover on points to view data.

Each 3d chart has a set of unique features:
- 14 cryptocurrency tokens
- 7 date ranges
- 6 variables visualized (variable 1)
- 6 variables visualized (variable 2)
- 5 line types
- 7 opacity settings
- many colors

Once a unique chart is created it will keep evolving with the latest data every time it is viewed. One point per day. Uses The Graph Sushiswap data (https://thegraph.com/explorer/subgraph?id=0x4bb4c1b0745ef7b4642feeccd0740dec417ca0a0-0). 

Real live data is visualized, hover on points for info.

⚠️ highly experimental ⚠️

metadata.name: pang #294
metadata.description:
Within each of us resides an evolutionary history of primal emotions, yet we often spend our lives dulling and controlling these instincts rather than reveling in them. Art is one of the ways we best express those instincts and intuitions – accessing and visualizing their visceral qualities, and releasing our deepest emotions in a way we can share.

pang reflects emotions that take control of our impulses – anguish, euphoria, obsession. By using crayon-like marks, the artworks convey the catharsis felt while drawing with a childlike abandon. To capture what gives such marks true feeling, the works deliberate the intrinsic movements, pressures, and angles shaped by hands in various moods. These qualities and their frenetic meanderings represent the infinite possibilities of where the crayon could go next – if only we could free ourselves from the layers of control we've built.

The contradictions we struggle with are reflected throughout the works:  in the long, methodical, and mathematical path to creation that yields work that looks fast, free and unrehearsed;  through the randomly-informed computer generation of art that feels human;  and by the depiction of long-standing traditional techniques to help display the conceptual range of a young, innovative art movement still establishing its pivotal place in the canon of art. These tensions parallel the work's underlying concept, accentuating the suspicion that a learned fear of emotional expression might just be the source of our own pang. 

Created in p5.js, pang is inspired by the emotional works and processes of later abstract expressionists such as Cy Twombly and Joan Mitchell – as well as contemporary artists like José Parla.

Functionality: 
Press ‘p’ to save as a png. 
Press ‘b’ to render with (or without) a transparent background.
Press 0-9 to render at varying degrees of quality.  0 (lowest quality) to 9 (highest quality, 15000 pixels lengthwise).
Press ⬆️ (arrow up) to incrementally increase pixel density.
Press ⬇️ (arrow down) to incrementally decrease pixel density.

__________
TENDER x abstractment
April 2022

metadata.name: Pandora #66
metadata.description:
Pandora received many gifts from the Gods: beauty, flattery, kindness, skill, grace, intelligence, but also the art of deception and seduction. They gave her the name Pandora (Πανδώρα), “endowed with all the gifts” in Greek.

The Pandora generative series has the same qualities as the mythological figure. Able to adopt many different shapes, a wide variety of colors and styles, all created from simple rules.

Only one thing though, do not open the box.

[S] key to save a PNG image
Press once for a resolution of 2000x2000, a second time for a resolution of 4000x4000, then 6000x6000 and finally 8000x8000

Made with p5.js

Artist: Estienne
April 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: Action Fields #69
metadata.description:
A generative painting based on abstract expressionism and the action paintings of Jackson Pollock.

Several different flow fields are used to create paths which are then painted in one of four different styles (pastel, paint, Pollock, black+gold). Additional features affect the background, path length + angles, level of detail, and mess (drips and splats). 

NOTES: 
- Some variations of the Pollock style may appear slightly different between browsers, but will render consistently in the same browser. 
- On slower devices, it may take some time to being drawing due to the background rendering.
- If you get a browser warning that the page is taking a long time, press continue.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1200x928px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 5,000 px. The ideal higher resolution is 2,000px.

metadata.name: Suspension #17
metadata.description:
Suspension uses simple objects to create structures suspended in space, held together by relation and composition.

The unique composition algorithm is random enough to produce infinite variations, but ordered enough to produce engaging artworks that are instantly recognizable.

Suspension uses negative space, additive coloring, and a unique rendering technique to create a very distinct style. 

It has many hand tuned palettes, with rare palettes that produce incisive variations.

Suspension is responsive and will render fast at any resolution. It looks great on wide screens of 2K, 4K or larger.

To accommodate the variation in displays, you can use the up/down arrow keys to adjust the brightness. 'r' resets to the default values.

's' will save an image in the exact size of the window, so you can create images in any resolution.

metadata.name: Gonzion #3
metadata.description:
Gonzion is a Non-Linear Iterated Function System rendered using a method similar to Fractal Flames of Electric Sheep fame.

Technological tendrils from beyond light-aeons draw ancient crystals, transmuted fungus, sentient sigils in fossilized dimensions and alien topologies.

It's not built to run on a (2022) mobile phone and has been known to crash some, but runs fine on others.

For higher resolution renders add "#N" to the URL, default N=2.
